Package oogasalad.engine.model.object

Class GameObject

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.engine.model.object.GameObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImmutableGameObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Entity, Player
public abstract class GameObject extends Object implements ImmutableGameObject
Abstract representation of a dynamic object in the game world.

Each GameObject has a unique identifier (UUID), type, position, velocity, hitbox for collisions, sprite data for rendering, and associated events and parameters.

It provides basic functionality like movement based on velocity and grounding logic, which can be extended by specific subclasses like Player, enemies, or environment objects.

Author:
Alana Zinkin

    • GameObject

      public GameObject(UUID uuid, String type, int layer, double xVelocity, double yVelocity, HitBox hitBox, Sprite spriteInfo, List<Event> events, Map<String,String> stringParams, Map<String,Double> doubleParams)
      Constructs a new GameObject with all necessary components.
      Parameters:
      uuid - unique identifier
      type - the category/type of the object (e.g., "Player", "Enemy")
      layer - rendering layer (used for draw order)
      xVelocity - initial horizontal velocity
      yVelocity - initial vertical velocity
      hitBox - spatial boundaries and collision area
      spriteInfo - visual rendering data for this object
      events - list of events associated with the object
      stringParams - string-based runtime parameters
      doubleParams - numeric runtime parameters
